    "created_at": "2015-03-23T23:26:08Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-03-23T23:26:08Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Looking some more at that code and how it's used, I don't think it's clearly separated enough from the Qt console to be worth releasing as a separate package. I'd advise you to either use an existing separate library like [pyte](http://pyte.readthedocs.org/en/latest/index.html), or to copy the `AnsiCodeProcessor` class into your own codebase and use and improve it as you go - potentially releasing it as a separate package when you're happy with how it's working.\n\nAt some point post-split, this functionality could be discarded from the Qt console in favour of relying on one of those packages.\n"
  },
